name: Medusae - Cotylorhiza Tuberculata
description: What can jellyfish teach us about climate change? Warming of temperatures, oxygen depletion and ocean acidification, coupled with overfishing and invasive species, are giving jellyfish advantage over other marine life. Cotylorhiza Tuberculata, or fried egg jellyfish, is is very typical of the Mediterranean and its sting has very little or no effect on humans.Half of the profit made with this series Medusae will be donated to WWF Mediterranean to help protect the Mediterranean Sea.
